# Rubberduck Repository Index

Indexes a Git repository using embeddings. Limited to JavaScript and TypeScript files at the moment.

## Development

### Prerequisites

```bash
brew install pnpm
```

### Setup

```bash
pnpm install
```

### Run

```bash
pnpm run-index --repository-path .
```

{
  "name": "@rubberduckai/repository-index",
  "version": "0.0.0",
  "private": false,
  "homepage": "https://github.com/rubberduck-ai/repository-index",

"ts-node": "10.9.1",
    "ts-node-dev": "2.0.0"
  },
  "dependencies": {
    "axios": "1.3.2",
    "commander": "10.0.0",
    "simple-git": "3.16.0",

runProgram({
  name: "Repository Index",
  configurationOptions: [
    new Option(
      "--repository-path <string>",
      "Git repository path"
    ).makeOptionMandatory(),

new Option(
      "--output-file <string>",
      "Name of the output file"
    ).makeOptionMandatory(),
    new Option("--open-ai-api-key <string>", "OpenAI API key")

(file.endsWith(".js") ||
      file.endsWith(".ts") ||
      file.endsWith(".tsx") ||
      file.endsWith(".sh") ||
      file.endsWith(".yaml") ||

file.endsWith(".yml") ||
      file.endsWith(".md") ||
      file.endsWith(".css") ||
      file.endsWith(".json") ||
      file.endsWith(".toml") ||

file.endsWith(".config")) &&
    !(
      file.endsWith(".min.js") ||
      file.endsWith(".min.css") ||
      file.endsWith("pnpm-lock.yaml")
    )

{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "strict": true,
    "declaration": true,
    "sourceMap": true,
    "target": "es2020",
    "lib": ["es2020"],
    "module": "commonjs",

"types": ["node"],
    "esModuleInterop": true,
    "allowSyntheticDefaultImports": true,
    "moduleResolution": "node",
    "rootDir": "./src",
    "outDir": "./build"
